.TH "imr_add_range" 9 "imr_add_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
imr_add_range \- add an Isolated Memory Region.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" imr_add_range
.BI "(phys_addr_t base "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "unsigned int rmask "  ","
.BI "unsigned int wmask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "base" 12
physical base address of region aligned to 1KiB.
.IP "size" 12
physical size of region in bytes must be aligned to 1KiB.
.IP "rmask" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "wmask" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success or negative value indicating error.
